# Example Project CLAUDE.md

This is what `/init-harness` generates for a typical TypeScript backend project.
Your actual CLAUDE.md will differ based on project analysis.

---

## Build

```bash
npm run dev          # Start dev server
npm run build        # Production build
npm run test         # Run tests (vitest)
npm run lint         # ESLint + Prettier check
npm run typecheck    # tsc --noEmit
```

## Architecture

- src/modules/{domain}/ — feature modules (controller, service, repository)
- Dependency direction: controller → service → repository (never reverse)
- No direct DB access from controllers
- All external calls wrapped in service layer

## Conventions

- Named exports only (no default exports)
- Error handling: custom AppError class, centralized error handler
- Naming: camelCase for variables/functions, PascalCase for types/classes
- Tests colocated: `src/modules/user/user.service.test.ts`

## Harness

### Hooks (`.claude/settings.local.json`)
- PostToolUse Edit|Write on `*.ts` → `tsc --noEmit` (blocking)
- PostToolUse Edit|Write on `*.test.ts` → `vitest run --reporter=verbose` (blocking)

### Traces
- `.claude/traces/evolution/` — harness change history
- `.claude/traces/failures/` — failure diagnosis (YAML: classification, resolved)
- `.claude/traces/search-set.md` — verification cases

### Change Strategy
Additive first → Subtractive → Structural. One change at a time.
Record all changes in `.claude/traces/evolution/` with verdict.
